## Review Scope

{{ review_scope | default("full") }}

**Named scopes** (defaults to `full` if not specified):

- `full` -- evaluate all eleven dimensions (FD1-FD11).
- `adapter_pr` -- focus on FD1 (Layering) + FD2 (A-rules) + FD3 (Security) + FD6 (Tests/conformance) + FD7 (Anti-Patterns). Use for any PR that adds or modifies a file under `frontend/lib/adapters/`.
- `ui_component_pr` -- focus on FD2 (U-rules + S-rules + the composer U_KBD/U_IME/U_AUTOSIZE/U_LBL/U_FOCUS_NO_STEAL hypotheses) + FD3 (Security/sandboxing) + FD4 (Accessibility) + FD5 (Performance/streaming) + FD7 (Anti-Patterns). Use for any PR that adds or modifies a file under `frontend/components/` or `frontend/app/`.
- `wire_translator_pr` -- focus on FD2 (W-rules + T-rules) + FD6 (wire schema drift). Use for any PR that adds or modifies a file under `frontend/lib/wire/`, `frontend/lib/trust-view/`, or `frontend/lib/translators/`.
- `security_audit` -- FD3 + FD7 only. Use for security-targeted reviews.
- `sprint_audit` -- FD8 + FD9 + FD11. Use for sprint-board re-derivation runs (e.g. before a release gate). FD8 walks the `Sprint Story Acceptance Map` row by row; FD9 runs `tests/architecture/test_middleware_layer.py`; FD11 records operational gaps (`monitoring.tf`, MFA, gated e2e). NEVER auto-rejects on its own — only inherits from FD9 (M-rules) which mirror FD1 severity.
- `infra_audit` -- FD10 + FD11 (and FD3.SEC1 / FE-AP-18 for the Cloudflare Pages env block). Use for any PR that adds or modifies a file under `infra/dev-tier/` or `tests/infra/`. FD10 dispatches to the per-test pytest nodes in `tests/infra/`; FD11 records the `monitoring.tf` and runbook gaps. The Cloudflare Pro WAF entitlement erratum is in the "Accepted V3 Deviations" allowlist — do NOT flag the absent 24h count-mode window.

